</div>

<p>It is a work-in-progress - things are still being changed, and new features and modules are being added quite frequently.</p>

<h2>Awesome. How do I use it?</h2>

<p>First of all, please note that Maraschino requires <strong>XBMC Frodo</strong>. It also doesn't support Internet Explorer at this time, in large part because it sucks balls. <a href="https://www.google.com/chrome/">Get a</a> <a href="http://www.firefox.com/">real</a> <a href="http://www.opera.com/">browser</a>.</p>
<p>Maraschino is written in Python and uses the Flask framework, so you need to configure a suitable web server (such as Apache) to serve it. If you're not comfortable configuring a web server then there is an easier installation method which uses CherryPy. You can also test it out first using Flask's built-in dev server if you like.</p>
<p>You can find setup instructions on the <a href="/installation">installation page</a>.</p>

<h2>Who created this?</h2>

<p>This project was started and is maintained by me (<a href="http://www.bradabrahams.co.uk/">Bradley Abrahams</a>) but many people have been so kind as to get involved and contribute code.</p>
<p>You can find them in the <a href="https://github.com/mrkipling/maraschino/blob/master/AUTHORS">AUTHORS</a> file of the GitHub repo. Big thanks to everybody that has contributed - Maraschino would not be the project that it is today without you!</p>



